articles.description: With the start of spring practice, Michigan State football coach Mark Dantonio sees this as a time for new beginnings in how the school handles claims of sexual assaults on campus.
articles.headline: Mark Dantonio hopes to play positive role in how MSU handles sexual assaults

images.caption: Michigan State football coach Mark Dantonio said Tuesday that he wants to "commit to be a part of the solution" for the campus' sexual assault problems.

articles.description: Kentucky head coach John Calipari says college players should be able to make money off their likeness and signature: "It's not ours, it's theirs."
articles.headline: Calipari: Players should be able to make money off their likeness

images.caption: John Calipari says the NCAA doesn't need to move slowly on the issue of college athletes making money off their likenesses and signatures.
images.name: John Calipari [600x400]

images.caption: Stephen A. Smith proposes a new players' association to fairly represent student-athletes and determine compensation.
images.name: Stephen A.: Student-athletes should form players' association

articles.description: The NIT will experiment with new rules, including a deeper 3-point line and a wider free throw lane.
articles.headline: NIT to experiment with new rules this season

images.caption: The NCAA 3-point line will stay at 20 feet, 9 inches, as the men's basketball rules committee decided against recommending a move back.
